body.name: Garmin Etrex 30 - REF
body.description: Our Most Popular Handheld GPS with 3-axis CompassWorldwide basemap2.2" 65K color, sunlight-readable display3-axis compass and barometric altimeterWireless capability to share waypoints, routes and geocaches with other similar devicesGPS and GLONASS satellites for faster positioningeTrex 30 takes one of the most popular and reliable GPS handhelds and makes it better. Enhanced ergonomics, an improved interface, paperless geocaching and expanded mapping capabilities makes eTrex more versatile and user-friendly, while maintaining its toughness and durability.See the WayeTrex 30 has an enhanced 2.2", 65K color, sunlight-readable display. Durable and waterproof, eTrex 30 is built to withstand the elements. It has an upgraded interface and stands strong against dust, dirt, humidity or water.New Tools for Your TrekeTrex 30 adds a built-in 3-axis tilt-compensated electronic compass, which shows your heading even when youre standing still, without holding it level. Also added is a barometric altimeter which tracks changes in pressure to pinpoint your precise altitude, and you even can use it to plot barometric pressure over time, which can help you keep an eye on changing weather conditions.Go AnywhereWith an array of compatible mounts, eTrex 30 is designed for use on ATVs, bicycles, in boats, as a handheld or in your car. Use the auto mount capability and City Navigator NT maps for turn-by-turn driving directions, or the rugged mount for your motorcycle or ATV. Wherever you think

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Couldn't be more pleased!
reviews.reviewText: From ordering to receiving, everything has been spot on. I registered with Garmin, and everything looks great. My purpose is to use on the PCT next year. I am in the process of looking for PCT toll maps to either down load, or get the ad card. Love the product, saved $100.00 by getting the refurbished, and it is as good as new, also received 1 year warranty.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked perfectly for what we needed (a good trail GPS)
reviews.reviewText: Worked perfectly for what we needed (a good trail GPS). Found some great free maps online to load which provided more details for trails. Disappointed on price and maps offered directly from Garmin, but luckily the community provides some good alternatives.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Birdseye not downloading
reviews.reviewText: I bought the device and during the weekend I purchased Birdseye maps since I was leaving early Monday morning. First off, I bought the map Saturday morning and was told it would take 24-48 hours for me to get the download e-mail. This was disappointing and it didn't make sense to me and there was no weekend support with which to contact. I kept checking online the rest of Saturday and most of Sunday and it said the order was pending. I finally checked my Spam folder Sunday night and it showed I received the order either late Saturday or Sunday morning (can't remember) but was disappointed the online status kept showing pending.I finally downloaded Birdseye but when I went to send the map to the device I kept getting an error that my device didn't have the prescription. I'm pretty computer proficient and tried various ways but kept getting locked. I tried calling Garmin from the airport Monday morning and they apologized but was unable to load the maps remotely. I'm back home and just tried to load the map again and it's still not loading. Unfortunately, I'm going to have to call sometime during the week to get this loaded.I'm rating the device a 3 because I was able to use it for some of the options but not fully.
